 sample. We explore the scenario that the evolution of AGN hosts is\ndriven by galaxy mergers and illustrate that an accurate assessment requires a\nlarger area survey since only three hosts may be undergoing a merger with\ntimescales <1 Gyr following a starburst phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Sep 2007 14:52:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 Mar 2008 19:01:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
